(422, 1, '2014-07-03 22:19:51', '2014-07-03 22:19:51', 'Riparian zones refer to the area that is next to water. The vegetation in healthy riparian zones plays an important role in maintaining the water quality. This provides many benefits for biodiversity (terrestrial species and neighbouring aquatic species), but there are, however, benefits for humans as well:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Improved water quality</strong> for recreational purposes, drinking water in wells and for livestock.</li>\r\n	<li><strong> Water absorption and storage</strong> – maintains water levels in wells, and prevents flooding</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Flood control</strong> — plants on the banks reduce the speed of moving water during storm events, resulting in decreased severity of flooding</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Protecting streambanks</strong> — prevents eroded soil from entering water</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Shade</strong> — helps to reduce water temperature, and increase habitat for species such as salmon, which are of interest to anglers.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Carbon sequestration</strong> — plants act as a carbon sink</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Shelterbelt</strong> — shrubs and trees act as a windbreak, reducing wind damage</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Riparian Area', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '184-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-03 22:19:51', '2014-07-03 22:19:51', '', 184, 'http://localhost/farming/?p=422', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
